Patch Set 11:

> (2 comments)
 > 
 > One question, see inline (same question in both places).

I guess config file wise it would not make a difference having them in the group or in the DEFAULT. AFAIK there is no way separating which options comes from which config file and even worse the config file parsing resolves duplicate entries very clearly by just overwriting anything with the latest provided.

For me it just makes easier to keep track of these when we don't try to overload the groups/values but if you feel strongly about it I'm fine for dropping the grouping.

Patch Set 11: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2

@Erno: Good point, and with all this options-in-code stuff, it's probably better to be explicit.  (Just thought it will look weird to have an empty DEFAULT group.  But if that's the weirdest thing about Glance, we're OK!)
